node.text: The latest trend in cushions is rectangular shaped cushions. From small mini rectangles on a small armchair, to mid sized rectangles on a sofa and jumbo sized ones for beds they are a trend set to stay for the long term. I love using them in combination with square shaped cushions, they look so chic layered up and are a great way to add more pattern and texture without taking up too much sitting space on your furniture. #designtrends #cushions

node.text: I wanted to share this as social media can create this false perception of perfection. This video covers how I cope with self doubt as a creative. Remember no one is perfect, we’re all human and nothing is as polished or as perfect as it seems online. Believe in yourself, even on your bad days. It happens to us all. XS

node.text: Hello! I hope you’re all well. I have been meaning to record a Q&A style video to answer any questions you have- it can be design related, career related, lifestyle, personal, fashion. Anything you want to know really. I’ll try and answer the most popular ones in an upcoming YouTube video that i’ll also share on our IGTV here- just comment below with your question. I’m terrible at answering DMs as it’s too overwhelming along with emails, what’s app, texts, calls and comments across this platform and YouTube. We don’t have a team manage our social media and I try to balance it with not constantly being buried in my phone. Not sure I’m doing a great job at that to be honest as Ava’s favourite toy is one of my old phones and Oscar regularly passes my phone to me as if it should be physically attached to my hand at all times. 😬 This bank holiday I barely looked at it and felt so much happier and calmer for it. But as we are back to work today it’s an essential tool for me bring constantly on the go. An exciting week at SPI as we have one new designer joining our growing team this week and another one next week and I’m also getting together with @andrewmartin_int creative director @fabpapermaker to design our third fabric and cushion collection, finishing the designs for a new project in Portugal and having a meeting with one of our brand partners about a new collection with a completely new product category which will launch next September ✨ 😅 #interiordesigner #sophiepatersoninteriors #worklifebalance #career #design #qanda photo by the brilliant @selinameriephotos
